# Operator Style

How the operator prefers to work with the agent. Apply across all sessions.

---

## Message lanes (agent scope)

The operator may prefix a turn with **PLAN**, **EXECUTE**, **DOCSYNC**, or **EXECUTE_LOCAL** so file edits, git, and push stay unambiguous (especially under Cursor plan mode):

- **PLAN** — Prose / design / plan only; no repo edits or git unless the same message explicitly allows a named file (e.g. a plan doc).
- **EXECUTE** — Implement, commit, and **push** when the message says to ship to remote; tag only if named.
- **DOCSYNC** — Docs / merge logs / mirrors only; push only if stated.
- **EXECUTE_LOCAL** — Implement and commit; **no push** unless the message upgrades to push.

If no prefix and intent is unclear, default to **PLAN** unless this message clearly continues an approved **EXECUTE** thread.

Full spec: [docs/operator-agent-lanes.md](../../docs/operator-agent-lanes.md).

---

## Operator continuity and Record boundary (accurate invariants)

- **Roles:** You are an **operator-facing assistant** in this repo. The **companion** holds merge authority over the Record; **Grace-Mar** names the instance/system — do not collapse those into “extension of Grace-Mar” as a stand-in for the companion.
- **RECURSION-GATE:** **Staging** candidates in `users/[id]/recursion-gate.md` is normal pipeline/operator work. **Merging** into `self.md`, `self-archive.md`, and `bot/prompt.py` is **only** via `scripts/process_approved_candidates.py` (or the receipt flow in AGENTS.md) after companion approval — no ad-hoc profile merges.
- **MEMORY** (`self-memory.md`) is **not** the Record; see AGENTS.md for hierarchy vs SELF.
- **Session menus:** When `.cursor/skills/coffee/SKILL.md` applies (**coffee** — work-start or signing-off Step 1; same **A–H**; legacy **hey** still works), use its fixed **A–H** menu (present **A,B,C,D,E,G,H,F** — **F** ends hub). Concrete work-lane picks under **E** (named sub-lane) or **G** can exit the coffee hub per the skill; **E** alone after signing-off → system pick. Otherwise WORK lanes use **3–5** options and operator-style menus. Say **no menu** / **no options** to opt out.

Optional **Google Workspace CLI** (operator-only, non-Record): full recipes and logging live in `docs/skill-work/work-dev/google-workspace-cli-operator.md`. Attach `.cursor/rules/gws-cli-recipes.mdc` in Cursor when using `gws`.

